<li id="cite_note-17"><b><a href="#cite_ref-17" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="book" id="CITEREFConze1993"><a href="/wiki/Edward_Conze" title="Edward Conze">Conze, Edward</a> (1993). <i>A Short History of Buddhism</i>. Oneworld. pp.&#160;14. <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/1851680667" class="internal">ISBN 1851680667</a>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=A+Short+History+of+Buddhism&amp;rft.aulast=Conze&amp;rft.aufirst=Edward&amp;rft.au=Conze%2C+Edward&amp;rft.date=1993&amp;rft.pages=pp.%26nbsp%3B14&amp;rft.pub=Oneworld&amp;rft.isbn=1851680667&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Soul"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-18"><b><a href="#cite_ref-18" title="">^</a></b> <a href="/wiki/B._Alan_Wallace" title="B. Alan Wallace">B. Alan Wallace</a>, <i>Contemplative Science.</i> University of Columbia Press, 2007, page 13.</li>
<li id="cite_note-19"><b><a href="#cite_ref-19" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/14153a.htm" class="external free" title="http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/14153a.htm" rel="nofollow">http://www.newadvent.org/cathen/14153a.htm</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-20"><b><a href="#cite_ref-20" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.vatican.va/archive/ccc_css/archive/catechism/p1s2c1p6.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.vatican.va/archive/ccc_css/archive/catechism/p1s2c1p6.htm" rel="nofollow">Catechism of the Catholic Church, paragraph 363</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-21"><b><a href="#cite_ref-21" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.vatican.va/archive/ccc_css/archive/catechism/p1s2c1p6.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.vatican.va/archive/ccc_css/archive/catechism/p1s2c1p6.htm" rel="nofollow">Catechism of the Catholic Church, paragraph 382</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-22"><b><a href="#cite_ref-22" title="">^</a></b> <i>Birmingham Amended Statement of Faith</i>. Available <a href="http://www.christadelphia.org/basf.htm" class="external text" title="http://www.christadelphia.org/basf.htm" rel="nofollow">online</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-23"><b><a href="#cite_ref-23" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://wikilivres.info/wiki/The_Holy_Qur%27an/Al-Hijr" class="external text" title="http://wikilivres.info/wiki/The_Holy_Qur%27an/Al-Hijr" rel="nofollow">The Holy Qur'an ~ 15. Al-Hijr (Stoneland, Rock City)</a> translation by <a href="/wiki/Abdullah_Yusuf_Ali" title="Abdullah Yusuf Ali">Abdullah Yusuf Ali</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-24"><b><a href="#cite_ref-24" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://wikilivres.info/wiki/The_Holy_Qur%27an/At-Tahrim" class="external text" title="http://wikilivres.info/wiki/The_Holy_Qur%27an/At-Tahrim" rel="nofollow">The Holy Qur'an ~ 66. At-Tahrim (Banning)</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-25"><b><a href="#cite_ref-25" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://wikilivres.info/wiki/The_Holy_Qur%27an/Az-Zumar" class="external text" title="http://wikilivres.info/wiki/The_Holy_Qur%27an/Az-Zumar" rel="nofollow">The Holy Qur'an ~ 39. Az-Zumar (The Troops, Throngs)</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-26"><b><a href="#cite_ref-26" title="">^</a></b> <i>Bhagvatisūtra</i>, (Ladnun: Jain Vishwa Bharti Institute):7/58,59</li>
<li id="cite_note-27"><b><a href="#cite_ref-27" title="">^</a></b> SGGS, M 1, p 1153.</li>
<li id="cite_note-28"><b><a href="#cite_ref-28" title="">^</a></b> SGGS, M 4, p 1325.</li>
<li id="cite_note-29"><b><a href="#cite_ref-29" title="">^</a></b> SGGS, M 1, p 1030.</li>
<li id="cite_note-30"><b><a href="#cite_ref-30" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.deathreference.com/Ce-Da/Chinese-Beliefs.html" class="external text" title="http://www.deathreference.com/Ce-Da/Chinese-Beliefs.html" rel="nofollow">Encyclopedia of Death and Dying (2008).</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-31"><b><a href="#cite_ref-31" title="">^</a></b> <cite style="font-style:normal" class="news">"<a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/18/science/18soul.html?8dpc=&amp;_r=1&amp;pagewanted=all" class="external text" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/18/science/18soul.html?8dpc=&amp;_r=1&amp;pagewanted=all" rel="nofollow">Found: An Ancient Monument to the Soul</a>". <i><a href="/wiki/New_York_Times" title="New York Times" class="mw-redirect">New York Times</a></i>. November 17, 2008<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/18/science/18soul.html?8dpc=&amp;_r=1&amp;pagewanted=all" class="external free" title="http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/18/science/18soul.html?8dpc=&amp;_r=1&amp;pagewanted=all" rel="nofollow">http://www.nytimes.com/2008/11/18/science/18soul.html?8dpc=&amp;_r=1&amp;pagewanted=all</a></span><span class="reference-accessdate">. Retrieved on 2008-11-18</span>.  "In a mountainous kingdom in what is now southeastern Turkey, there lived in the eighth century B.C. a royal official, Kuttamuwa, who oversaw the completion of an inscribed stone monument, or stele, to be erected upon his death. The words instructed mourners to commemorate his life and afterlife with feasts “for my soul that is in this stele.”"</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Found%3A+An+Ancient+Monument+to+the+Soul&amp;rft.jtitle=%5B%5BNew+York+Times%5D%5D&amp;rft.date=November+17%2C+2008&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2008%2F11%2F18%2Fscience%2F18soul.html%3F8dpc%3D%26_r%3D1%26pagewanted%3Dall&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Soul"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
<li id="cite_note-32"><b><a href="#cite_ref-32" title="">^</a></b> artsci.wustl.edu/~philos/events/conferences/FutureMindBrain.doc</li>
<li id="cite_note-33"><b><a href="#cite_ref-33" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://chem.tufts.edu/AnswersInScience/MethodologicalNaturalism.htm" class="external free" title="http://chem.tufts.edu/AnswersInScience/MethodologicalNaturalism.htm" rel="nofollow">http://chem.tufts.edu/AnswersInScience/MethodologicalNaturalism.htm</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-34"><b><a href="#cite_ref-34" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.amazon.com/dp/0140145346/" class="external free" title="http://www.amazon.com/dp/0140145346/" rel="nofollow">http://www.amazon.com/dp/0140145346/</a></li>
